Edward,<br>
Thank you for the honor of including me in your statement.<br>
 you said....<br><br>
&quot;it is just that you and I, today, face different enemy<br>
targets.. ignorance, greed, immorality, and mistruths.&quot;<br><br>
We always faced those enemies, then and now. I am glad<br>
that we here are fighting against the common enemy that<br>
you describe, for you would be a fierce enemy that I would<br>
rather not have to oppose.<br><br>
As an American, I wish that I could give the medals to those<br>
who deserved, but did not get the recognition for your<br>
valor. What no one can take from you is the fact that you<br>
did what you did and know it for what it was. Take that knowledge<br>
and use it every day. There is strength in knowing oyu<br>
did what had to be done, when it needed to be done.<br>
Right on!<br><br>

